# External Link Rules for City Pages

## Clickable links — housing portals ONLY

The only section that renders clickable links is **Housing → Where to search**.
All other sections use plain-text search guidance — no clickable links.

| Section | Rendering |
|---|---|
| Housing portals | ✅ Clickable link (`isVerified: true` required) |
| Schools | 🔍 Google search link (system-generated, never a stored URL) |
| Visa officialLink | 📝 Plain text: `Search "[label]" for official details` |
| Community | 📝 Plain text: `Search '[name]' on Facebook` |
| Sources footer | ✅ Clickable link (`isVerified: true` required) |

## SearchHint — universal fallback for non-housing links

Everywhere a link is NOT a verified housing portal root, use `<SearchHint query="..." />` instead of `<a href="...">`.

`SearchHint` renders:
```
Search: "[query]"   [🔍 Search on Google]
```

The button generates `https://www.google.com/search?q=[encoded query]` at render time — never stored, never stale.

### Query format rules

| Section | Query format |
|---|---|
| Schools | `"[School Name] [City] [Country]"` |
| Visa | `"[visa type] [country] official"` — use the `officialLink.label` |
| Community | stored in `communityLinks[].searchQuery`, e.g. `"Valencia Expats Facebook group"` |

### isVerified — required on housing and sources links only

Set `"isVerified": true` on housing portal URLs and source URLs before they render as links.

```json
// ✅ Housing portal — clickable
{ "label": "Idealista", "url": "https://www.idealista.com", "isVerified": true }

// ✅ Source — clickable
{ "label": "Numbeo Valencia", "url": "https://www.numbeo.com/cost-of-living/in/Valencia", "isVerified": true }
```

**Never add `isVerified` to schools, visa officialLinks, or communityLinks** — the renderer ignores URLs in those sections entirely and uses `SearchHint` instead.

## Housing portal links — root URLs only

Never use filtered search results, city-scoped pages, or paginated URLs.

```json
// ❌ BAD — deep search result URL
{ "label": "Idealista Valencia", "url": "https://www.idealista.com/en/alquiler-viviendas/valencia/", "isVerified": true }

// ✅ GOOD — stable root
{ "label": "Idealista", "url": "https://www.idealista.com", "isVerified": true }
```

## Schools — use category types only, never named institutions

School names cannot be trusted. Institutions close, rename, or change. Use `options[]` with category descriptions, not `examples[]` with named schools.

```json
// ❌ BAD — specific school name that may not exist or may have changed
{ "name": "ACE International School", "curriculum": "British", "fees": "฿120,000/yr" }

// ✅ GOOD — category description, honest, no entity risk
{
  "type": "British curriculum international schools",
  "description": "Small selection serving expat community. Limited spots.",
  "fees": "฿120,000–280,000/year typical"
}
```

The renderer auto-generates `SearchHint` with query `"[type] [city] [country]"`. No URLs needed.

## Visa officialLink — label only, no url required

The renderer shows `Search "[label]" for official details` as plain text. The `url` field is stored as dormant data but never rendered. Only provide a label.

```json
// ✅ GOOD
{ "label": "Spain Digital Nomad Visa official" }
```

## Community links — text guidance only, no url field

```json
// ❌ BAD — url ignored, creates confusion
{ "label": "Valencia Expats", "url": "https://www.facebook.com/groups/..." }

// ✅ GOOD — label IS the search instruction
{ "label": "Search 'Valencia Expats' on Facebook — on-the-ground advice from residents" }
```

## searchPortalsIntro — required format for every city

```json
"searchPortalsIntro": [
  "These are local rental platforms — this is where residents rent long-term housing (cheaper than Airbnb).",
  "Search '[City Name]' inside each platform to filter local listings.",
  "Tip: [city-specific short-stay advice]."
]
```

## Applies to

- `data/cities.json` and `data/countries.json`
- All future city pages
